    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Durin",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/dcdf547f543afd251efe7723477446d3_3871269587163042268.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Millenniums ago, there was a kingdom called Sal Vindagnyr. Once upon a time, the priests of the kingdom could touch the heavens and go to the Abyss at the request of the gods of Celestia. On the mountain, a white tree grew, which was part of Irminsul. The High Priest and Priestess of Vindagnyr a daughter with the gift of foresight. One of her prophecies was the coming of the Black Dragon, who would poison everything with his venom. Then the kingdom was destroyed by the Skyfrost Nail and turned into ruins, and the white tree withered. For many years, no one set foot on these snow-covered peaks until the princess's prophecy began to come true.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The alchemist Rhinedottir, also known as Gold, created many beasts from the Abyss that soon attacked all seven kingdoms of Teyvat. Durin was one of Rhinedottir's children, created in the form of a black serpent-dragon with wings.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Then, my lovely children,",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Like rainwater flowing into creeks, and plants growing towards the sun,",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Go unto a lovely place, and display your own beauty there with pride.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "One day, Durin heard Anemo Archon Barbatos playing his lyre and saw the dragon Dvalin. He was fascinated by the beauty of music. Durin dreamed that he had gone on a long, long journey, into a land where green grass grew and where soulful songs were sung. He dreamed that he sang along with the gentle people of this land and danced in the skies with a dragon as beauteous as a jewel.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Thank you, Mother, thank you.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"You gave me wings to soar and a mighty form.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Mother, I wish to go to a land of lovely songs,\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"I will tell them about you, Mother, and about everyone else.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"I shall tell them that the place where I was born is beautiful.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/3dd966675be0cb2d46c420ae09c0bf6d_7816181422405867650.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Durin went to Mondstadt to meet the beautiful dragon and the bard, but he did not know that his blood was poisonous and that it would be toxic to people and land. Although he did not mean to cause any harm, he became a real disaster for Mondstadt. The people of Mondstadt believed that he wanted to destroy all living things. The envy of the devilish dragon gave rise to evil that poisoned the land and the people who lived on it. In those terrible days, bloodthirsty monsters and desolation came to Mondstadt. Awoken from his sylvan slumber by the cries of Durin's victims, the Anemo Archon came forth and summoned his faithful servant to his side. For life and for freedom, the Archon and the Wind Dragon rode the wind to face their foe. In a battle that ripped clouds from the skies, Dvalin spread his six blessed wings wide, severing the sky and tearing through Durin's iron scales with the force of a colossal blade. As the conflict plunged the world into darkness, the Wind Dragon struck out with his claws, like swords forged of wind, and they pierced deep into Durin's dark, corrupt flesh. The battle shook the heavens, even the sun quaked with fear. Finally, Dvalin tore out Durin's throat with his teeth, and the evil dragon fell from the sky.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Farewell, Mother! My journey is ended.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"I shall sleep beneath this white, shining silver... and perhaps this, too, is good.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Farewell, O lovely bard! And farewell, O lovely dragon!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Would that we had met in a different time and place,\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"To meet, to sing and dance together!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "So he thought most sincerely as he lay dying.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Now then, this great blessing that pulses through my veins,\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"And the lovely sight of the dark universe that gave me birth...\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"They are now yours to inherit.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/f5cdefaf93f3fc5a8efaa9d8e670b325_8501016490997682825.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Durin's body fell on the ruins of the ancient kingdom of Sal Vindagnyr, which has since been called the Dragonspine. The snow on the top of the mountains never melts, so the forces of eternal ice were able to contain the poison of decay exuding from Durin's body. His poisoned heart still beats deep in the snow. The blood poisoned the land and gave strength to the monsters living",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/d97160c2d7ebb6560f691f24e5ac57f6_1075917967524094745.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "there. Durin's will to live is capable of resurrecting dead plants and turning them into monsters like the Cryo Regisvine. When the blood of the Black Dragon Durin spilled onto the land of Vindagnyr and the Traveler nourished the dead white tree with Crimson Agates that arose from the blood of the dragon, the long-dead tree at the top of the mountain was reborn again.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/07/23/237301566/e5c9d34ce04ae089c791a20cce528f0d_6757926172519614298.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "After Durin's death, Andersdotter, a witch from the Hexenzirkel, created a version of Durin in a magical world called Simulanka. Although she knew that the real Durin's fate will be connected with Durin of Simulanka, she hoped that one day he will have his own path. Like the real Durin, a dragon of the magical world destroyed everything he touched, and people feared him. When he wished never to be born at all, a few heroes from Teyvat appeared in Simulanka and saved the dragon. When Andersdotter was creating Durin of Simulanka, her son, another witch Barbeloth made a prophecy about Teyvat's Durin:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"R's child... will one day rise from the dead.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Recent observations at Dragonspine lend credence to this prophecy, and Durin's heart has slowly but surely been growing in vitality. The process is extremely slow, but the trend is clear. Albedo, Durin's brother, hopes that when the time comes, Simulanka's Durin will lend Mondstadt a hand in their hour of need.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3796,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/04/26/169177528/a19531bd8e93b793b79bfe1499b5b5d7_1821424930343002645.png",
                      "name": "Mondstadt",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
