                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Chalk Prince and the Dragon",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "One day a blacksmith forged a magical sword, onto which he applied the ground claws, fangs, and scales of Durin. The dragon's venom penetrated the sword, giving it special powers. The blacksmith was so proud of his creation that he decided to test the sword himself. As soon as he entered battle, the energy of decay rushed up the hilt and entered his body. Mere mortals could not resist this force. The cursed and insane blacksmith fled in a fit of insanity and may have met his end in an unknown place.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/27/237301566/20f19930548c5c93f9b91aa2fc6276cd_2030450059687261741.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "This sword came to Albedo, one of Rhinedottir's children and Durin's brother. Albedo wanted to conduct several experiments, but during his research, he unexpectedly learned the history of the sword. This sword was almost \"alive\" and was capable of absorbing others' energy. Knowing that ordinary people could not use this sword, Albedo gave it to the Traveler, who had the power to neutralize Durin's poison, so that they would imbue the sword with life force. Albedo then drew this force from the sword, which was found to resonate with him due to their kinship with Durin.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 47,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/character/Albedo_icon.png",
                      "name": "Albedo",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2011,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/weapon/腐殖之剑.png",
                      "name": "Festering Desire",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 1492,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/object/Festering Dragon Marrow_icon.png",
                      "name": "Festering Dragon Marrow",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Shadows Amidst Snowstorms",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "When the alchemist Rhinedottir was conducting her experiments to create life with the help of Khemia, one of her experiments failed and was thrown away. It was swallowed by the dragon Durin, and after the dragon was defeated in the eternal ice and snow, the experiment came to life, fed with Durin's blood. The failed experiment became jealous of Albedo, who was almost perfect in its eyes, so it decided to transform into Albedo and take his place. Albedo was able to stop his doppelganger, but its further fate is unknown.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
